Package com.pandora.general.objects.services.abstractions.interfaces

package com.pandora.general.objects.services.abstractions.interfaces
This package contains a set of interfaces defining abstractions for various services related to freshwater biogeochemistry within the Pandora framework. These interfaces provide a common contract for classes implementing specific functionalities, such as CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations, managing maps, and handling different types of data associated with freshwater systems.

The key interfaces in this package are:

  • CrudService:

    Defines CRUD operations for managing entities within the Pandora framework.

  • MapService:

    Specifies operations for managing maps, including cleaning or resetting the map state.

  • DischargesMapService:

    Extends MapService and includes methods for finding and saving discharge data associated with specific cells and time steps.

  • TerrestrialSourcesMapService:

    Extends MapService and provides methods for handling terrestrial sources data associated with cells and time steps.

  • UpstreamSourcesMapService:

    Extends MapService and includes methods for finding and saving upstream sources data, as well as handling additional data for specific time steps and final states.

  • VolumesMapService:

    Extends MapService and offers operations for finding and saving volume data associated with specific cells and time steps.

  • YMapService:

    Extends MapService and defines methods for managing state variable data, including finding and saving data associated with specific cells and time steps.

  • Interfaces
    Class
    Description
    CrudService<T,ID>
    The CrudService interface defines generic CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations for managing entities of type T with identifiers of type ID.
    DischargesMapService
    The DischargesMapService interface extends the MapService interface and defines methods for managing discharge values associated with specific Cell locations and LocalDateTime timestamps.
    MapService
    The MapService interface defines a common method for cleaning or resetting the map managed by the service.
    TerrestrialSourcesMapService
    The TerrestrialSourcesMapService interface extends the MapService interface and defines methods for managing terrestrial sources data associated with specific Cell locations and LocalDateTime timestamps.
    UpstreamSourcesMapService
    The UpstreamSourcesMapService interface extends the MapService interface and defines methods for managing upstream sources data associated with specific Cell locations and LocalDateTime timestamps.
    VolumesMapService
    The VolumesMapService interface extends the MapService interface and defines methods for managing volume data associated with specific Cell locations and LocalDateTime timestamps.
    YMapService
    The YMapService interface extends the MapService interface and defines methods for managing state variable data associated with specific Cell locations and LocalDateTime timestamps.
